---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About KnowYourStatus" description="What KnowYourStatus is, how it works, and our editorial standards.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-8" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6">About KnowYourStatus</h1>

    <section class="prose mb-10">
      <h2>What this project is</h2>
      <p>
        KnowYourStatus is a free, open-source reference site covering common legal questions immigrants face in the United States. Every page links directly to the primary legal source — a federal statute, regulation (Code of Federal Regulations), or official government agency page — so readers can verify information themselves instead of relying solely on our summary.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site covers work authorization, college applications, housing, healthcare, banking, driving, and many other areas of law that affect immigrants' daily lives. It is maintained by volunteers and is not affiliated with any government agency, law firm, or bar association. It is not a substitute for legal advice.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="prose mb-10">
      <h2>Who runs it</h2>
      <p>
        Maintained by [Name]. Content reviewed by [Reviewer or "Pending attorney review"].
      </p>
      <p>
        We are actively seeking licensed immigration attorneys and DOJ-accredited representatives who are willing to review topic pages before they are published. If you can help, please see the <a href="/contribute">Contribute</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Editorial standards</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold mt-0.5">1.</span>
          <span>Every factual claim on a topic page links to a primary source — a statute, regulation, or official page on a .gov domain — or to an authoritative secondary source such as a law school clinic, the American Immigration Lawyers Association (AILA), CLINIC, or a legal aid organization.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold mt-0.5">2.</span>
          <span>Reddit, Quora, personal blogs, law firm marketing pages, and AI-generated content are not cited.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold mt-0.5">3.</span>
          <span>Every page shows a "Last verified" date. Pages are re-verified at least every 6 months and immediately when a relevant regulation changes.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold mt-0.5">4.</span>
          <span>Pages are reviewed by a second human before publication. Ideally a licensed immigration attorney or DOJ-accredited representative reviews the page before it is marked verified.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold mt-0.5">5.</span>
          <span>The site provides legal information, not legal advice. It does not use AI-generated content and carries no advertising. It does not create an attorney-client relationship.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="prose mb-10">
      <h2>How verification works</h2>
      <p>
        Each topic page displays a "Last verified" date and the name of the person who verified it. Before a page is published with a verified date, a second reviewer (ideally a licensed immigration attorney or DOJ-accredited representative) must confirm that the primary sources cited are still accurate and current.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pages with <code>verifiedBy: "Pending review"</code> have been drafted but not yet confirmed by a second reviewer. Treat these pages with additional caution.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="prose mb-10">
      <h2>License and contribution</h2>
      <p>
        Site content (the topic pages and other written material) is licensed under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 (CC BY 4.0)</a>.
        The site code is licensed under the <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MIT License</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        To suggest a correction or contribute a new topic, see the <a href="/contribute">Contribute</a> page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <aside role="note" class="p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-900 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
      <strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-slate-200">Disclaimer:</strong> This site provides legal information, not legal advice. Nothing here creates an attorney-client relationship. Consult a licensed immigration attorney or <a href="/find-legal-help" class="text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 underline hover:text-blue-900">accredited representative</a> for advice specific to your situation.
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
